{"word":"συνωνέομαι","slug":"συνωνέομαι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>συνωνέομαι</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>ήσομαι</el>) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><a href='S:Deponent Verb, i.e. a Verb of Middle or Passive form with Active sense'>Dep.</a> <i>to collect by offering money</i>, <el>ς. ἵππον</el> <i>to hire a body of</i> cavalry, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to buy up</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>coemere</el>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:—the <a href='S:perfect tense'>perf.</a> <el>συνεώνημαι</el> is <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a>, <el>ὁ συνεωνημένος σῖτος</el> corn <i>bought up</i> <b><a href='S:Lysias'>Lys.</a></b>; but <a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>act.</a></a> in <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}